descriptionMarkdown:
This blueprint provides a factory subunit that manufactures advanced circuits. 

Placement
-------------

The subunit can be tiled in two dimensions. In the North/South direction, one row of beacons should overlap with beacons already placed to create parallel tracks. In the East/West direction, the cells can extend along the same track: the first/last column (containing the vertical track elements for side-loading) should overlap with an already-placed column of track elements. 

An 8x5 array of these factory cells with all modules installed will produce approximately 6500 advanced circuits/minute. 

Operation
-------------

Copper plates must be sent to the bottom-most track. Advanced circuits are delivered via the top-most track. If desired, you can reverse the direction of this top-most track to send output in the same direction as the input. 

There are three tracks through the middle of the cell; the top and bottom of these three tracks must be loaded with one of plastic or green cards, and the middle track loaded with the opposite resource. 

It would take a very large number of these cells in a linear configuration to consume all resources off of express tracks, so the two tracks with the same resource can be easily fed from a single main stream with a splitter.
title: Advanced (Red) Circuit Factory Cell (2d tileable)
